      "writtenOn": "2021-01-26T13:25:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Guess what, I missed lack of () here, even though I wrote the exact same code. So, your code was and is indeed correct as func was a side effect. Sorry.\n\nNow, wrt doing transaction right here: you are exactly right in your analysis (or at least it 100% matches mine). So, yes, I think it\u0027s OK to end up temporarily in such a state. However, I think let\u0027s land as is and observe. It may work just fine as a side effect.",
